{"questionId":"10661","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Bromine and methanoic acid react in aqueous solution.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Br<sub>2</sub> (aq) + HCOOH (aq) → 2Br<sup>−</sup> (aq) + 2H<sup>+</sup> (aq) + CO<sub>2</sub> (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The reaction was monitored by measuring the volume of carbon dioxide produced as time<br>progressed.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/678d23bae9495ae4a3337049953f74911a3c8d7b.png\" width=\"701\" height=\"486\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Outline, with a reason, another property that could be monitored to measure the rate of this reaction.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1</strong></em><br>colour&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong><br>Br2 /reactant is coloured «Br<sup>–</sup> (aq) is not»&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2</strong></em><br>conductivity&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">[✔]</strong><br>greater/increased concentration of ions in products&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-